 WinPEAS & LinPEAS

1. Overview
PEAS (Privilege Escalation Awesome Scripts) is a set of post-exploitation enumeration tools used to discover privilege escalation vectors.

- LinPEAS: For Linux privilege escalation  
- WinPEAS: For Windows privilege escalation  

Used in:
- Pentesting  
- Red teaming  
- CTFs  
- Internal audits  

---

2. Key Features
WinPEAS
- Detect weak Windows services  
- Find credentials in memory  
- Check for vulnerable software  
- Identify misconfigured permissions  
- Search for stored passwords  

LinPEAS
- Detect kernel exploits  
- Check SUID binaries  
- Identify writable files  
- Detect exposed credentials  
- Find cron jobs, capabilities, PATH issues  

---

3. Installation

Linux — LinPEAS
  curl -L https://github.com/peass-ng/PEASS-ng/releases/download/20241231/linpeas.sh -o linpeas.sh
  chmod +x linpeas.sh
  ./linpeas.sh

Windows — WinPEAS

Download:
https://github.com/peass-ng/PEASS-ng/releases

Run:

winpeas.exe

---

4. Useful Commands
LinPEAS
./linpeas.sh
./linpeas.sh -a    # Aggressive mode

WinPEAS
winpeas.exe
winpeas.exe quiet

---

5. What LinPEAS Detects
  Kernel vulnerabilities
  World-writable files
  SUID/SGID abuse
  PATH hijacking
  Docker breakout vectors
  Credential leaks
  SSH key exposure

---

6. What WinPEAS Detects
Unquoted service paths
Weak service permissions
Credential Manager secrets
Registry credentials
Scheduled tasks
Writable startup folders
